README - global information (start here!)

Notebook last re-run: 2014-07-12 14:43:22.863746

We analyze 13 regions (corresponding to 5? filaments) on Tycho's synchrotron rims.
Energy bands are: 0.7-1 keV, 1-1.7 keV, 2-3 keV, 3-4.5 keV, 4.5-7 keV.

For regions 2, 6, 8, 9, 11 (5 of 13), we did not calculate a FWHM for the 0.7-1 keV band. In these regions the FWHM was either not resolved or barely resolved; e.g., if taking a FWHM measured from the data maximum was not possible within the fit domain, we discarded said measurement.

The southern rim was faint and complicated by multiple filaments (mush...). But it may be worth revisiting to check. The western rim was strong at high energies, but showed clear line emission. However this was not investigated with our spectra from divided rim/downstream regions.

Average FWHMs plotted as a function of energy

Globally averaged FWHMs (normalized to 2-3 keV value) plotted vs. energy.
Left: mean of normalized FWHMs (normalize within each region, then average)
Right: normalized mean FWHMs (average, then normalize among averages)
Plotted errors = 1 std. dev. of normalized FWHMs. No error bar on 2-3 keVvalue in left plot as normalized FWHMs are all unity (std. dev. = 0)

Procedure

Each filament consists of 2-5 regions (filament 1, 5; the rest have 2 right now).
For each filament, I present a zoomed image of each filament + region selections,
a plot of FHWMs vs. energy for regions in each filament,
and a table of FWHM values and an average exponent m_E, following Ressler et al.

Each region has two sets of plots: 1st row shows profile fits/FWHM locations,
2nd row shows shaded boxes (overlaid on 4.5-7 keV data) corresponding to extracted spectra locations.
All spectra fitted with absorbed powerlaw (XSPEC: phabs*po).

More details on fits/spectra/etc

We fit thin rims to a two-exponential model of form:

$$h_{up}(x) = A_u \exp \left(\frac{x_0-x}{w_u}\right) + C_u$$
$$h_{down}(x) = A_d \exp \left(\frac{x - x_0}{w_d}\right) + C_d$$

Each band's fit domain is bounded at the first minimum downstream of the bright rim. We smooth the radial profiles in each band to identify said minimum. Upstream, the fit domain is set by the region's bounding box.

We extract spectra from two regions (blue, gray).
The blue region spans the leftmost fit domain bound to the leftmost FWHM bound (in any band), on the rim's downstream side.
The gray region extends from the blue region's edge to the rightmost FWHM (in any band) on the rim's upstream side.

Spectra are from full ~750 ks exposure, data binned with >=15 counts.
